During the 2020-2021 school year, the VCS Social Services Team is able to provide food for students in need over the weekend.

Food items will be provided to students on the last school day of each week to sustain the student through the weekend.

If you would like your student(s) to participate in the Backpack & Snacks Program, please click this link: https://forms.gle/NKL3gDCHUKS3pSkQ6

Students who previously participated in the Backpacks & Snacks Program must be signed up again in order to receive food bags this school year.

The 1st Backpacks & Snacks distribution for this year will be on Friday, August 21st.

post_text: So many wonderful extracurricular teams and clubs at VHS! Check them out in the slide show below accompanied by the Varsity Singers rendition of the school song, ‚ÄúThe Green and White - Valparaiso High School Victory Song‚Äù.
shared_text:
Valpo HS 411
April 23 at 5:48 PM ¬∑

Attached is a slide show of some of our VHS Extra Curricular Teams and Clubs with a recording of "The Green and White - Valparaiso High School Victory Song" sung by the Varsity Singers. The Varsity Singers were planning on recording the VHS School Song in a studio setting during the second semester. With the recent transition to remote learning, they were able to modify this plan and use the program "Soundtrap" to record individual students' voices from their homes. After collecting these recordings, Mr. Riegle and Mr. Luke were able to mix these individual recordings together into this recording. We are sure this will lift your school spirits!

Attached is a slide show of some of our VHS Extra Curricular Teams and Clubs with a recording of "The Green and White - Valparaiso High School Victory Song" sung by the Varsity Singers. The Varsity Singers were planning on recording the VHS School Song in a studio setting during the second semester. With the recent transition to remote learning, they were able to modify this plan and use the program "Soundtrap" to record individual students' voices from their homes. After collecting these recordings, Mr. Riegle and Mr. Luke were able to mix these individual recordings together into this recording. We are sure this will lift your school spirits!
